<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-850] Infinite looping of closures with at least two patameters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-850</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On the current CVS buid groovy-1.0-jsr-02-SNAPSHOT,&lt;br/&gt;
there has been found an Infinite Looping Bug of closures with&lt;br/&gt;
at least two parameters.&lt;br/&gt;
Stack Overflows are produced, because of Infinite Looping Bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is an example code for test:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;println &quot;Testing a closure with one parameter:&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
def c1 = &lt;/p&gt;
{ x -&amp;gt; return (x + 1) }
&lt;p&gt;println c1(4)           // work&lt;br/&gt;
assert c1(4) == 5       // work&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;println &quot;Testing a closure with two parameters:&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
def c2 = &lt;/p&gt;
{ x, y -&amp;gt; return (x + y) }
&lt;p&gt;println c2(3, 4)            // not work!  infinite loop&lt;br/&gt;
assert c2(3, 4) == 7        // not work!  infinite loop&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;println &quot;Testing a closure with three parameters:&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
def c3 = &lt;/p&gt;
{ x, y, z -&amp;gt; return (x * y * z) }
&lt;p&gt;println c3(8, 9, 10)            // not work!  infinite loop&lt;br/&gt;
assert c3(8, 9, 10) == 720      // not work!  infinite loop&lt;/p&gt;</description>
